Osama bin Laden was a son of the Saudi parent whose radical campaign to recreate a seventh-century Muslim empire presented a threat of terrorism to the US.
With the attacks on the World Trade Center and the Pentagon on Sept. 11, 2001, Bin Laden was elevated to the realm of evil in the American imagination once reserved for dictators like Hitler and Stalin. He was a new national enemy, his face on wanted posters, gloating on video, taunting the United States and Western civilization.Added doc: 498010994-2 : please divide this sentence into shingles and test it like this please

